<br>
 yes.  in that case your username would be seen as you on the message board bam! thats half right there.  <br>
<br>
and yes. in that case you could use lots and lots of proxies to hide yourself.  if your good you can search for proxies and feed them to your checker as you go.  <br>
<br>
but in that case even then the person has to make an eductated guess as far as what your password looks like.  its about time.  <br>
<br>
someone may have a password that is &quot;1aD3ihDG238sAju@&quot; they exist. if you got &quot;usernameSam&quot; that might be his password you dont know.  on the other hand &quot;usernameSam&quot; might have a password of &quot;GoSam&quot;  .  but again you dont know.<br>
<br>
What you do know is that you have a few 100 usernames you pulled off the message boards (again this was back in the day).  So what you do is you have your <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="httpchecker..">cker..</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> (and there are checkers out there.  just search hacking passport accounts via hotmail.. ewwww passport gross)  anyway.  you have to have your checker basically assume one of the people on the list has a weak password of the form:<br>
-syllabels.  the idea here is you use combinations of sylabels in a dictionary instead combinations of random letters (this could snag magykmarker even though its big)<br>
-words from the dictionary tacked on to the front or back of a random sequence are a Big O of (c) time multiplied to that sequence (in other words the words tacked on dont really count<br>
-no caps if its longer then small<br>
-no numbers if its longer then small<br>
- being small (just try them all if they are small)<br>
<br>
So basically if your username is one of the ones on the hackers list if it had a few non syllabel pieces in the password a few numbers and a few caps (hell if your going to be lazy use all caps) and its sufficiently large the hacker still wouldnt nail you (though note that dictionary words on the leading side or trailing side dont really count as size).  to be clear not cause your password is impossible (though you would be a long ways to make it number crunch wise impossible do away with all sylabels from a dictionary make it 12 characters long with caps and numbers and it is pretty close) but because the hacker doesnt have time to check all the usernames on his list with that kind of thoroughness.  the hacker is looking for a weak password to speed up his/her search.<br>
<br>
so this is a ya:<br>
back when your username and password was on the station accounts could and did get hacked because of the above.  but thats been gone for a while.<br>
