<br>
When I was hacked i got some information out of the GM as to who might have done it.  Basically during the same time that I was hacked another person on Quellious had the exact same thing happen to them.  Both of us were logged on from the same IP adress during that time and no we don't know each other at all.  All three of our IP adresses are in the same range and network.  Basically the conclusion I came to was that someone that probably worked at my ISP was able to sniff packets going to the log on server and that the encryption being used between the client and log on server was weak and broken.  I changed ISP's and never had another problem.<br>
<br>
I don't know what algorithms are used by the log on server, but it is my opinion that they are very crackable. <p><a href="http://www.lotuscult.com"target=_blank>Lotus Cult </a><BR><img src="http://www.lotuscult.com/~gimily/clerics.jpg"><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21865" target=_blank>Gimily's Gear</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ueadrictheranger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eadric the Ranger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/3/02 2:49:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~F'ing hackers~</span><hr size=1> that's interesting Gimily, and i bet it could explain a lot of the hacking incidents where people had not given their account info to anyone (much more plausable than brute force).  it seems the connection between your isp and the login server is indeed hackable, and i can't say that surprises me at all.  though some isp's will be more hackable than others, it's always going to be a weak spot, and weak spots are what hackers target.  figuring out someones IP is not difficult if they log into a msg board or other traceable site, as long as they stay online - once the hacker has your IP, the stuff they can do to you is pretty scary <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  anyone have any suggestions on how to protect ourselves from this type of hacking?<br>
